<h2><span style="background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;">Podium Chat POC Test</span></h2>
<p><span style="background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;">1. In order to have chat available, an agent must be online in Salesforce and assigned to a queue within Omni-Channel Supervisor. Additionally, assigning skills will allow your reps to take Chats for certain customer tiers, and Products.</span></p>
<p><span style="background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;">2. Start a chat, enter in contact details (use one that already exists in SF with a tier) for it to route correctly. An agent in SF should have that skill and available to accept the chat, or you will see the chat waiting in the Skills Backlog.</span></p>
<p><span style="background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;">3. Chat should open, to person with correct skills. Chat should relate to the contact in Salesforce (If no contact is in Salesforce, no contact will be assigned) and a case will be created/related to the Chat.</span></p>
<p><span style="background-color: #000000; color: #ffffff;">4. Work the chat, close the chat, then close the related case or follow up with them via email.</span></p>
  
	
embedded_svc.settings.prepopulatedPrechatFields = { "FirstName": *firstName*, "LastName": *lastName*, "Email": *email*}; //Sets the auto-population of pre-chat form fields
	


